task.title: Expanding the Navigator in increments

indexterm.keyword: Expanding Child Items at the platform level of the Navigator

context.p: When clicking Expand on a Navigator branch of more than, by default, 25 child items, you are prompted to enter the number to expand at one time.

step.cmd: Set the number of items to expand:

substep.cmd: If the Expand child items window is not open, right-click the Navigator item whose child items you want to expand incrementally and click Expand .
Enter the number to expand and click OK to open that number of child items.
Click Morewhen you want to open the next group of child items.

step.cmd: Expand child items. You can expand all the child items of a Navigator item. The entire branch does not expand, just the children of the selected item. If the Expand child items window is not open, right-click the Navigator item whose child items you want to expand and click Expand Child Items.

table.title: Example: Expansion limit of 4 for the Windows Server child items

example.p: This example illustrates the result of selecting Expand Child Items at the platform level of the Navigator. The site is monitoring 500 Windows-based systems. The user can quickly see which systems have situation events and at what severity.
